# Hotsite Spec Format

Each spec lives at `docs/specs/SPEC-###-slug/` and contains:

- `spec.md`
- `meta.yaml`

## Required `spec.md` frontmatter

```yaml
---
id: SPEC-###
title: Human-readable title
category: scaffold | section | integration | quality | release
status: draft | ready | in_progress | review | done | blocked | cancelled
---
```

## Required body sections

1. Objective
2. Context and traceability
3. Scope
4. Out of scope
5. User experience
6. Functional requirements
7. Non-functional requirements
8. Content contract
9. Visual and responsive behavior
10. Technical contract
11. Expected file changes
12. Analytics and SEO impact
13. Accessibility requirements
14. Acceptance criteria
15. Test plan
16. Risks and open questions
17. Definition of done

Requirements must be atomic, testable, and uniquely identified.
Acceptance criteria must describe observable outcomes, not implementation steps.
